    Am J Clin Nutr
    Important food sources of fructose-containing sugars and adiposity: A systematic review and meta-analysis of controlled feeding trials.
Energy control and food sources mediate the effect of fructose-containing sugars on adiposity. The evidence provides a good indication that excess energy from sugars (particularly SSBs at high doses =20%E or 100 g/d) increase adiposity, whereas their removal decrease adiposity. Most other food sources had no effect, with some showing decreases (particularly fruits at lower doses =10%E or 50 g/d).
